arma

Enum Op

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Op>
      • arma.Op
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Op>

    public enum Op
extends java.lang.Enum<Op>

    Provides constants for the following operators.

    Arithmetic operators:
    PLUS, MINUS, TIMES, ELEMTIMES, DIVIDE, ELEMDIVIDE

    Relational operators:
    EQUAL, NOT_EQUAL, STRICT_LESS, LESS, STRICT_GREATER , GREATER

    Author:
    Sebastian Niemann

      • evaluate

        public static Mat evaluate(Mat a,
           Op operator,
           Mat b)
                    throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException,
                           java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Non-canonical: Creates a column vector containing a 1 for each element for which an element-wise evaluation of a operator b holds true and a 0 otherwise.
        Parameters:
        a - The left-hand side operand.
        operator - The operator to be used.
        b - The right-hand side operand.
        Returns:
        The created column vector.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - Non-canonical: Thrown if another operator besides relational operators is provided.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Non-canonical: Thrown if both arguments are matrices but have an unequal number of elements.
